<subSubSection id="FB9B543705937D21EE4388C6F23665D3" pageId="15" pageNumber="54" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="9FB8F1057D1D64F97161F7789F600D32" pageId="15" pageNumber="54">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E36E6133A319A02F7065E77D6F8622E" pageId="15" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="480DCC0508FFC06AFA99C8D7954A4DBE" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="54">modesta</emphasis>
(Latin) = moderate, presumably referring to the culms of average height.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6CF72609F7CC43EA2C2AFA6333701DD9" pageId="15" pageNumber="54" type="nomenclatural comments">
<paragraph id="F2B550872A8609D82DE9819F418CCA90" pageId="15" pageNumber="54">Nomenclatural comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="04132B3664D3194F31EFE0E8F4F733C2" pageId="15" pageNumber="54">
The locality information given by 
<bibRefCitation id="50EF14EBC430C1D962BA3FAB7A10CB78" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/1218786" author="Connor, HE" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="26" pageNumber="65" pagination="595 - 605" refId="B10" refString="Connor, HE, Edgar, E, 1974. Names and types in Cortaderia Stapf (Gramineae). Taxon 23: 595 - 605, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/1218786" title="Names and types in Cortaderia Stapf (Gramineae)." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/1218786" volume="23" year="1974">Connor and Edgar (1974)</bibRefCitation>
is incorrect. Note that Glaziou made several collections of the same species from the same area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
